### visitTypeBegin() {#a409fe6a584117eab814a4f2ba281b865}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>Error LVTypeVisitor::visitTypeBegin (<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/codeview/#a238eda31f74c0f0f3224f71b50b7d165">CVType</a> &amp; Record)</>}
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
Paired begin/end actions for all types.

Receives all record data, including the fixed-length record prefix. <a href="#a409fe6a584117eab814a4f2ba281b865">visitTypeBegin()</a> should return the type of the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/record">Record</a>, or an error if it cannot be determined. Exactly one of the two visitTypeBegin methods will be called, depending on whether records are being visited sequentially or randomly. An implementation should be prepared to handle both (or assert if it can&#39;t handle random access visitation).

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/logicalview/include/llvm/debuginfo/logicalview/readers/lvcodeviewvisitor-h/#l00068">68</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/debuginfo/include/llvm/debuginfo/logicalview/include/llvm/debuginfo/logicalview/readers/lvcodeviewvisitor-h">LVCodeViewVisitor.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/readers/lvcodeviewvisitor-cpp/#l00485">485</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/debuginfo/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/lib/debuginfo/logicalview/readers/lvcodeviewvisitor-cpp">LVCodeViewVisitor.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
